The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms to improve and automate the construction of neural networks, which falls under the category of neural evolution (cs.NE). The focus is on convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their use in image classification, which suggests the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of evolutionary algorithms to optimize neural networks is a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and the discussion of the framework's potential applications in specific areas suggests the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
